Nah. Interspecies breeding works with Pokemon rules. The offspring is always the species of the mother with more superficial traits inherited from the father.

This system is clean, simple, and avoids potentially disturbing scenarios where a mother would give birth to something markedly dissimilar from her own anatomy.
